+# 2026-06-09 Selection Layout Scroll Runtime Validation
+
+## VALIDATED
+- Runtime/browser validation completed with seeded mock data.
+- Runtime used:
+  - API: `http://localhost:5291` with `TfsIntegration__UseMockClient=true`
+  - Client: `http://localhost:5292`
+  - Profile: `1` (`Commander Elena Marquez`)
+- Route validated: `/planning/plan-board/portfolio`
+
+Scenario outcomes:
+1. Baseline: **PASS** (aligned baseline at axis 970, Incident 959, Crew 959)
+2. Select small epic (`Emergency Alert Distribution - User Interface`): **FAIL** (Incident jumped to 405)
+3. Select large epic (`Crew Location Tracking - Data Processing Pipeline`): **FAIL** (Crew drifted to 783 while Incident stayed at 405)
+4. Deselect: **FAIL** (scroll positions stayed drifted)
+5. Selection switch (A -> B): **FAIL** (drift persisted; no recovery)
+6. Regression sweep (move earlier/later, duration +/-, undo, focus, pin, current sprint marker): **FAIL** (alignment drift persisted; Incident changed to 0 during focused state)
+
+## SCROLL POSITION TABLE
+| Scenario | axis scrollLeft | Incident scrollLeft | Crew scrollLeft | Comparison vs previous defect (970 / 405 / 959) |
+| --- | ---: | ---: | ---: | --- |
+| 1. Baseline | 970 | 959 | 959 | Not in defect state |
+| 2. Small epic select | 970 | 405 | 959 | **Matches previous defect exactly** |
+| 3. Large epic select | 970 | 405 | 783 | Incident defect persists + crew drift |
+| 4. Deselect | 970 | 405 | 783 | Defect persists |
+| 5. Selection switch | 970 | 405 | 783 | Defect persists |
+| 6. Regression sweep | 970 | 0 | 783 | Worse drift in focused regression state |
+
+Defect status:
+- **The 959 -> 405 defect still occurs.**
+- It reproduced in Scenario 2 and remained present through subsequent scenarios.
+
+## SCREENSHOTS
+All screenshots below were captured during this runtime session and are stored in-repo under `docs/reports/assets/2026-06-09-selection-layout-scroll-runtime-validation/`.
+- `docs/reports/assets/2026-06-09-selection-layout-scroll-runtime-validation/validation-selection-scroll-01-baseline.png`
+- `docs/reports/assets/2026-06-09-selection-layout-scroll-runtime-validation/validation-selection-scroll-02-small-epic.png`
+- `docs/reports/assets/2026-06-09-selection-layout-scroll-runtime-validation/validation-selection-scroll-03-large-epic.png`
+- `docs/reports/assets/2026-06-09-selection-layout-scroll-runtime-validation/validation-selection-scroll-04-deselect.png`
+- `docs/reports/assets/2026-06-09-selection-layout-scroll-runtime-validation/validation-selection-scroll-05-selection-switch.png`
+- `docs/reports/assets/2026-06-09-selection-layout-scroll-runtime-validation/validation-selection-scroll-06-regression-sweep.png`
+
+## FAILURES
+- Blocking regression reproduced: selecting `Emergency Alert Distribution - User Interface` still causes Incident timeline jump `959 -> 405` while axis remains at `970`.
+- Additional drift observed after switching to the large epic: Crew timeline changed to `783`.
+- Deselect and selection-switch flows did not restore alignment.
+- Regression sweep preserved functional actions, but scroll alignment remained incorrect and Incident changed to `0` in focused-state verification.
+
+## REGRESSION CHECKS
+Verified interaction flows executed in runtime:
+- Move earlier: executed
+- Move later: executed
+- Duration increase: executed
+- Duration decrease: executed
+- Undo: executed
+- Focus: executed (`Focus` -> `Exit focus`)
+- Pin: executed (`Pin` -> `Unpin`)
+- Current sprint marker: present in axis during scenarios
+
+Result: interaction controls remain callable, but alignment regression remains unresolved.
+
+## RISK
+- **High:** the core selection-layout scroll-preservation defect remains reproducible.
+- **High:** row-specific drift persists across scenario transitions, creating cross-row misalignment risk.
+- **Medium:** regression actions are available but do not mitigate the drift state.
+
+## NEXT PROMPT CONTEXT
+- Validation was runtime-only and used the local mock setup with profile 1.
+- Baseline starts aligned at `(axis=970, Incident=959, Crew=959)`.
+- Selecting the small epic immediately reproduces the old defect state `(970, 405, 959)`.
+- Selecting the large epic adds crew drift `(970, 405, 783)`.
+- Deselect and selection switching do not recover alignment.
+- A blocking regression is documented; no implementation changes were made in this validation task.
